President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Peter M. Haymond as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the Lao People's Democratic Republic. Haymond, a career member of the Senior Foreign Service, currently serves as Chargé d'Affaires at the United States Embassy in Bangkok, Thailand. He has over 30 years of experience in the Foreign Service and has held various positions, including Director of the State Department's Office of Chinese and Mongolian Affairs and Consul General at the United States Consulate in Chengdu, China.

Additionally, Kelly C. Degnan has been nominated as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to Georgia. Degnan, also a career member of the Senior Foreign Service, currently serves as the Political Advisor to the Commander of United States Naval Forces Europe – United States Naval Forces Africa. She has held various positions throughout her 25-year career, including Deputy Chief of Mission of the United States Mission to Italy and Political Counselor at the United States Mission to the North Atlantic Treaty Organization in Brussels, Belgium.

Both nominees have extensive experience in diplomatic roles and have earned various awards and recognition for their service.